## 5. Interactive Features

### Answer Checking System

#### State Management
```typescript
// User answers stored in React state
const [answers, setAnswers] = useState<Record<string, string>>({});

// Results after checking
const [results, setResults] = useState<CheckResults | null>(null);

// Whether to show visual feedback
const [showResults, setShowResults] = useState(false);
```

#### Validation Logic
```typescript
// Location: /src/utils/answerChecker.ts

normalize(answer) {
  - Trim whitespace
  - Convert to lowercase
  - Collapse multiple spaces
  - Remove trailing punctuation
}

checkAnswer(id, userAnswer) {
  - Fetch correct answer from ANSWER_KEY
  - Normalize both
  - Compare
  - Handle arrays (multiple correct answers)
  - Return boolean
}

checkAllAnswers(userAnswers) {
  - Loop through all answer IDs
  - Check each answer
  - Calculate statistics
  - Return CheckResults object
}
```

